Q) Two sum- Given an array of integers nums and an integer target, return indices of the two numbers such that they add up to target.

Create a hashmap  -> interate through the array, take num, target-num as renum, check if renum is in hashmap, if not -> put answer ans[0] as renum and ans[1] as its index,
if it exists, update the map

class Solution {
    public int[] twoSum(int[] nums, int target) {
        HashMap <Integer, Integer> map =new HashMap<>();
        int[] ans = new int[2];
        int n= nums.length;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            int num=nums[i];
            int renum = target-num;
            
            if(map.containsKey(renum)){
                ans[0]=map.get(renum);
                ans[1]=i;
            }
            else{
                map.put(num,i);
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
